{
  "article_title": "FORMULATION OF METFORMIN HYDROCHLORIDE SUSTAINED RELEASE MATRIX TABLET AND VALIDATION BY IN-VITRO EQUIVALENCE STUDIES",
  "sections": {
    "abstract": "The study developed a Metformin HCl sustained-release matrix tablet using wet granulation with Eudragit RSPO, HPMC, and Xantural 75. Physical parameters complied with BP/USP. In vitro equivalence (biowaiver) showed similarity to innovator (Glucophage) with f2 > 62 in pH 1.2, 4.5, 6.8. Release kinetics fitted quadratic model. Stable under accelerated conditions.",
    "introduction": "Background on type 2 diabetes, metformin pharmacology, need for SR formulation, polymers (HPMC, Xantural 75, Eudragit RSPO) and release mechanisms.",
    "materials_and_methods": "Described in Experimental section.",
    "results_and_discussion": "Detailed in Results and Discussion.",
    "conclusion": "Formulation H was equivalent to innovator with better drug release; stable for 6 months."
  },
  "materials_origin": {
